node.title: Tesla Files Legal Papers to Officially Move Headquarters to Austin, Texas
node.alt: Tesla is moving its headquarters from Palo Alto, California to Austin, Texas. Here, the Tesla logo can be seen on a charging station.
node.description: The auto company owned by Elon Musk was previously headquartered in Palo Alto, California.
node.content:
["Tech giant Tesla, Inc. filed paperwork Wednesday to officially move their headquarters to Austin, Texas.", "The company released its report filed with the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC) stating that the brand will now be run from their 'gigafactory' located near Austin-Bergstrom International Airport.", "Owned by the richest person in the world, South African-born Elon Musk, Tesla has previously been headquartered in Palo Alto, California throughout its lifespan.", "Musk stated during a shareholder meeting this past October that he was planning on an exile from the brand's California headquarters in favor of Austin.", "This is a breaking news story and will be updated with additional information. ", "", "
Tesla is moving its headquarters from Palo Alto, California to Austin, Texas. Here, the Tesla logo can be seen on a charging station.
"]
